& [SLMLLMProviderAdapterContract] is the lower LLM evidence adapter contract
  + [contract_uuid] is 59a5ba3b-c461-4856-a544-b377ec02dfd7
  + [slice_id] is SLM-04
  + [depends_on] is SLM_Core_Data_Contracts
  + [status] is accepted_for_provider_deliberation_contracts

  & [ProviderAdapter] is the exchange boundary for lower LLM evidence
    + [provider_id] is stable local provider identity
    + [model_id] is model name or version
    + [adapter_kind] is mock, lm_studio_openai_compatible, ollama, llama_cpp_server, hosted_openai_compatible, or extension
    + [capability] is dictionary_service, role_suggestion, candidate_meaning, candidate_relation, faculty_run, objection, answer, or jury_review
    + [prompt_contract] is required for non-mock provider calls
    + [response_hash] is required when response body is preserved or summarized
    + [timestamp] is required when live provider is used
    + [adapter_version] is required
    = must: return evidence records, not graph objects
    = must: preserve provider provenance with every suggestion
    = must: support deterministic MockProvider for SOP and implementation tests

  & [ProviderSuggestion] is evidence emitted by a ProviderAdapter
    + [suggestion_id] is unique in EvidenceWorkspace
    + [provider_provenance] is required
    + [suggestion_kind] is grammar_role, lexical_sense, candidate_meaning, candidate_relation, faculty_vote, objection, answer, or jury_measurement
    + [support_weight] is optional provider-supplied support
    + [natural_language_rationale] is optional but required for objection and answer
    + [provider_faculty_report] is optional structured internal seven-faculty validation evidence
    + [lineage] is input prompt, token refs, and prompt contract
    - never: create Glyph directly

  & [MockProviderRequirement] is the v0 determinism rule
    = must: define at least one mock provider before live provider integration
    = should: define two mock providers with intentional disagreement for wobble and deliberation testing
    = must: allow provider_set behavior without requiring real model calls

  ! [Slice04Complete] is accepted
    @ [support] adapter boundary allows LM Studio, Ollama, llama.cpp server, hosted providers, and mocks without changing semantic graph rules
    @ [support_delta] SLM-27 defines provider internal faculty report payloads for future live adapters
